				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Anyone here a business traveler?<a name="50946"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 9 04 1:09 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I've been on the road for the past 5 years or so and most of my playtime is from a hotel room.
<br />

<br />
The only time I've ever had trouble (using both AoL as my nationwide ISP and using compuserve) is that some hotels you'll be unable to connect through the phone at faster than 26.6. 
<br />

<br />
It seems to be indemic to the hotel chosen and their phone system not sure why or how.  For instance in Detroit you may be at a motel 6 that connects 56.6 over the phone and the Hilton next door connect at 18.7.
<br />

<br />
the second trouble that you can run in to is that you may have to dial a 9,,, to allow for dial outside access.  But EQ can run even at a 26.6 connect although in high lag situations like a raid, it can get a bit spacey.
<br />

<br />
and like a poster said above..Double check to see what a local call will cost ya!</span></td>
