				<td colspan="2"><span>You can do this with a lot of cell phones. Many cell phones have a PC link cable available and can act as a wireless modem as long as you're paying your cell phone carrier for wireless data access (usually $3-5 per month plus airtime). I do this with my Verizon LG 4400 when I'm in a real bind and need net access rapidly. Depending on your carrier and region, though, it could be slow... dial-up speeds in a lot of areas.</span></td>
