				<td colspan="2"><span>Now that I moved to Boulder, I'm going back to being a traveling minstrel.  Imho, Starbucks/Panera/Borders/Your local sports bar with wireless connections seem to be faster and with fewer disconnects than any hotel except the ones with cable LAN high speed connections.  I have at times used my cell phone (Motorola V60) as a modem and gotten faster connections.  I have eleventybillion cell minutes but if you don't, using your cell phone as a modem will quickly eat your time.  Also beware of whether you're roaming or not.
